title: KLASIFIKASI EMOSI PADA CUITAN DI TWITTER DENGAN PRINCIPAL COMPONENT ANALYSIS DAN SUPPORT VECTOR MACHINE
Tweets Emotions Analysis of Community Activities Restriction as COVID-19 Policy in Indonesia Using Support Vector Machine
summary: The results of the emotion classification onPPKM tweets reveal that most Indonesians are unhappy with the implementation of the PPKM policy, higher than those obtained by previous studies.

title: BejaGNN: behavior-based Java malware detection via graph neural network
summary: Experimental results on a public Java bytecode benchmark demonstrate that BejaGNN achieves high F1 98.8% and is superior to existing Java malware detection approaches, which verifies the promise of graph neural network inJava malware detection.
authors: Pengbin Feng,Li Yang,D. Lu,Ning Xi,Jianfeng Ma

title: From task to evaluation: an automatic text summarization review
summary: This review examines the difference between the task format and the evaluation metrics in automatic summarization, and specifically focuses on the between readability and fluency and consistency.
authors: Lingfeng Lu,Yang Liu,Weiqiang Xu,Huakang Li,Guozi Sun

title: DPMS: Data-Driven Promotional Management System of Universities Using Deep Learning on Social Media
summary: The proposed Data-Driven Promotional Management System (DPMS) for universities is the first promotional management system for universities and demonstrates significant potential for improving the brand value of universities and for increasing the intake rate.
authors: M. E. Hossain,Nuruzzaman Faruqui,Imran Mahmud,Tony Jan,Md. Whaiduzzaman,Alistair Barros

title: Computational Models to Study Language Processing in the Human Brain: A Survey
summary: Analysis of efforts in using computational models for brain research reveals that no single model outperforms others on all datasets, underscoring the need for rich testing datasets and rigid experimental control to draw robust conclusions in studies involving computational models.
authors: Shaonan Wang,Jingyuan Sun,Yunhao Zhang,Nan Lin,Marie-Francine Moens,Chengqing Zong

title: GlareShell: Graph learning-based PHP webshell detection for web server of industrial internet
authors: Pengbin Feng,Dawei Wei,Qiaoyang Li,Qin Wang,Youbing Hu,Ning Xi,Jianfeng Ma
